The paper discusses a framework for reasoning about conditional probabilities in machine learning without making strong assumptions about the underlying distributions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning and structured prediction, which are common topics in the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the estimation of marginals, which is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
